Thanks for addressing my previous comment Stuart.

Just a curiosity question. 

I understand that this fix is to prevent credentials being exposed through logs.

But why fixing the same for migration scripts as well? 

Removing the URI from the script log, on exception, might not give me a clue of which image_location record is causing the problem. Because there is only reason left in the log message now. Do you think it would be better to print the image_id as well as part of the log message?

Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

I would rather prefer having this info in the logs. However, if majority prefer otherwise :- this is an important fix and we should have clear consensus across Openstack projects with this idea of not logging sensitive info in debug in general.

There is a corresponding bug in python-keystoneclient that I'm aware about which is discussion in progress. There were multiple PS at one point however, now seems a narrow set but Abandoned as many folks do not like this idea. Please refer here:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/horizon/+bug/1004114
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/42467/

There are many deployments which reply on debugging hickups from these logs. So, may be we should have a broader audience reviewing this.

Patch Set 8:

At today's IRC meeting we reached a consensus to print out the image id for the migrate scripts. I took a look and unfortunately it may not be that easy to print the image_id. All you have to work with at that point in the code is a uri which is known to be malformed.

In light of that, are we ok with PS8?
